      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): apply stale-run liveness check to aborted subagent orphan recovery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix #90766: stale subagent runs (>2h) with `abortedLastRun: true` were exempt from stale-unended pruning, causing very old aborted child sessions to be resurrected after long gateway downtime.\n\nChanges:\n- **`subagent-registry-helpers.ts`**: Remove the `abortedLastRun` exemption from `resolveSubagentRunOrphanReason` — stale aborted runs are now classified as `stale-unended-run` like any other stale run\n- **`subagent-orphan-recovery.ts`**: Add `isStaleUnendedSubagentRun` check before attempting recovery; await `finalizeInterruptedSubagentRun` and report `failedRuns` when finalization does not update the registry (scheduler retry path)\n- **`subagent-orphan-recovery.test.ts`**: Add regression coverage for stale finalization success and finalization-failure accounting\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Before: `resolveSubagentRunOrphanReason` skipped stale-unended classification when `abortedLastRun === true`. `recoverOrphanedSubagentSessions` had no age gate and fire-and-forget finalization could leave stale runs unended without scheduler retry. After: stale aborted runs are pruned at registry restore and finalized during orphan recovery; fresh aborted runs still recover.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, production functions via `node --import tsx` and focused Vitest.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nProduction liveness helper (stale vs fresh cutoff):\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { isStaleUnendedSubagentRun } from './src/agents/subagent-run-liveness.ts';\nconst now = Date.now();\nconst TWO_HOURS = 2 * 60 * 60 * 1000;\nconst stale = { createdAt: now - 3 * TWO_HOURS, startedAt: now - 3 * TWO_HOURS };\nconst fresh = { createdAt: now - 30 * 60 * 1000, startedAt: now - 30 * 60 * 1000 };\nconsole.log('stale aborted (3h):', isStaleUnendedSubagentRun(stale, now));\nconsole.log('fresh aborted (30m):', isStaleUnendedSubagentRun(fresh, now));\n\"\n```\n\nOrphan recovery + persistence regression:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/subagent-orphan-recovery.test.ts src/agents/subagent-registry.persistence.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nstale aborted (3h): true\nfresh aborted (30m): false\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  39 passed (39)\n```\n\nNew orphan-recovery tests confirm:\n- stale aborted run (`startedAt` 3h ago) calls `finalizeInterruptedSubagentRun`, does not resume via gateway\n- finalization returning `0` increments `failed` and populates `failedRuns` for scheduler retry\n- fresh aborted run (`startedAt` 55s ago) still resumes normally (existing test)\n\n**Observed result after the fix:** Stale aborted subagent runs (>2h, no `endedAt`) are finalized instead of resurrected after gateway restart. Fresh aborted runs (<2h) continue through orphan recovery. Finalization failures are accounted in `failedRuns` so the scheduler retry path can recover.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live gateway with multi-hour downtime and real LLM-backed subagents (default stale window is 2h).\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- User-visible behavior changed: Yes — very old aborted subagent runs (>2h) will be finalized instead of resurrected after gateway restart\n- Config, environment, or migration change: No\n- Security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution change: No\n- Highest-risk area: Session-state cutoff for restart-aborted child sessions older than the stale window; fresh aborted runs are unchanged\n- Mitigation: Shared `isStaleUnendedSubagentRun` policy used at both registry restore and orphan recovery; await finalization + `failedRuns` accounting; persistence + orphan-recovery regression tests (39/39 pass)\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action: `@clawsweeper re-review` after P2 finalization-accounting fix and expanded proof\nWaiting on: `proof: sufficient`, `rating: 🦞 diamond lobster`\nBot comments addressed: P2 await-finalization finding fixed in `8ebc547a5e8`\n\nFixes: #90766\n",
        "branch": "fix/90766-orphan-recovery-stale-runs",
